Biography - James O'Hern

James O'Hern, Secretary of State of Illinois, and ex-officio Superintendent of Public Instruction, is among the leading men of the Prairie State. Born near Lawrence, Kansas, October 21, 1852, he spent his boyhood on the home farm and attended the public schools. He completed his education at Trinity College, Dublin, Ireland, where he took his degree in 1874, winning the gold medal for essay writing. After graduation Mr. O'Hern began his business career as a teacher in the public schools of Chicago. In 1881 he was appointed Superintendent of Chicago Police, under Mayor Harrison. Mr. O'Hern brought to that office a ripe experience with men and affairs, and a training which he bent to the service of the city with most gratifying results. The same year he was elected Sheriff of Cook County, and was re-elected in 1884. In 1887 he was again a candidato for Mayor of Chicago. In 1889 Mr. O'Hern was named a member of the Democratic National Committee, and in 1890 was appointed Collector of the Port of Chicago. He was a prominent candidate for Secretary of State at the State Convention of 1892, and was elected to that position the following year. He was a delegate to the National Democratic Convention in 1896, and is at this writing (1900) a prominent candidate for Mayor of Chicago. Mr. O'Hern possesses many of the qualities which go to make up a great political leader. He is a logical and forceful thinker, and he knows how to express his thoughts clearly and forcibly. He is possessed of a rare gift of oratory. He has a thorough training and fine scholarship, and is a man of delightful social qualities. Mr. O'Hern is the author of several books. In 1887 he published "The Irish in America," a work which attracted much attention and was severely criticised by certain organs of the Ancient Order of Hibernians. In the same year appeared "The Other Side," in which the author replied to his critics. He also wrote a life of William O'Brien, the Irish patriot. Mr. O'Hern possesses a pleasing personality and is an entertaining writer. He is a man of large intellectual ability, and a student of men and affairs. He is a forceful speaker, and is popular alike in public and private life.

namespace Modules\Terminals\Observers;

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Cache;
use Modules\Terminals\Entities\Terminal;

class TerminalObserver
{
    /**
     * Handle the Terminal "created" event.
     *
     * @param Terminal $terminal
     * @return void
     */
    public function created(Terminal $terminal)
    {
        Cache::forget('terminals');
    }

    /**
     * Handle the Terminal "updated" event.
     *
     * @param Terminal $terminal
     * @return void
     */
    public function updated(Terminal $terminal)
    {
        Cache::forget('terminals');
    }

    /**
     * Handle the Terminal "deleted" event.
     *
     * @param Terminal $terminal
     * @return void
     */
    public function deleted(Terminal $terminal)
    {
        Cache::forget('terminals');
    }
}

PAPEETE, le 22 mars 2016- Une cargaison de 90 kilos de cocaïne a été interceptée samedi par la marine polynésienne sur un voilier en provenance des côtes chiliennes. Les cinq occupants du voilier, deux chiliens et trois péruviens, ont été placés en garde à vue.

Samedi, en début d'après-midi, la marine nationale en Polynésie française a réalisé une saisie de près de 90 kilos de cocaïne à une centaine de miles nautiques dans le sud-ouest de Fakarava. Le voilier suspect, repéré par un Falcon 200 de la flotille 25F basée à Tahiti, était suivi depuis quelques jours par les moyens de surveillance de la marine nationale. L'intervention des moyens maritimes a été déclenchée samedi à 14h10 par le lancement d'un hélicoptère Dauphin de l'escadrille 35F.

A son arrivée sur zone, le Dauphin intercepte le voilier et contraint les suspects à se rendre avant qu'ils n'aient le temps de jeter ces stupéfiants par-dessus bord. 24 ballots de cocaïne, d'un poids total de près de 90 kilos, et 250 litres de gasoil sont saisis à bord.

Les cinq suspects, deux chiliens et trois péruviens, ont été interpellés et placés en garde à vue à la gendarmerie de Papeete. Cette nouvelle saisie de drogue vient confirmer la vigilance des moyens de surveillance déployés par la marine nationale et des services douaniers pour lutter contre les trafics de stupéfiants en Polynésie française.

The latest poll shows that only 34% of American adults believe Joe Biden is doing a good job as president. That’s down from 59% in April 2021. His approval rating has been declining steadily since then, and it’s now at its lowest point since he took office.

There are a number of reasons for Biden’s declining popularity. One is the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic. The pandemic has caused economic hardship for many Americans, and it has also led to a great deal of uncertainty and anxiety. Biden has been criticized for his handling of the pandemic, and some people feel that he has not done enough to help Americans through this difficult time.

Another reason for Biden’s declining popularity is the rise of inflation. Inflation has been rising steadily in recent months, and it is now at its highest level in decades. This is making it more difficult for Americans to afford basic necessities, and it is causing financial hardship for many families. Biden has been criticized for his policies, which some people believe have contributed to inflation.

Finally, Biden’s popularity has also been hurt by the ongoing war in Ukraine. The war has caused a great deal of uncertainty and anxiety around the world, and it has also led to higher energy prices. Biden has been criticized for his handling of the war, and some people feel that he has not done enough to support Ukraine.

Biden’s declining popularity is a serious problem for his presidency. If he does not improve his approval ratings, it will be difficult for him to pass his legislative agenda and to lead the country effectively.

Фильтр HEPA - высокоэффективный воздушный фильтр, способный задерживать до 99,97% взвешенных частиц размером свыше 0,3 мкм (таких как пыльца, споры грибов, бактерии, частицы табачного дыма, шерсть животных и т.п.). HEPA фильтры, в основном, используются в системе приточно-вытяжной вентиляции, для фильтрования наружного воздуха, подаваемого в помещение, в медицинской и фармацевтической промышленности, а также для защиты оптических и компьютерных систем. HEPA фильтры изготавливают путем наложения слоев мелкопористого фильтрующего материала друг на друга, что создает хаотичную структуру волокон, замедляющую движение частиц и тем самым обеспечивая эффективную фильтрацию. В ВОЗ есть классификация HEPA фильтров по четырем классам, в зависимости от эффективности задержания частиц: * H10 - 85% * H11 - 95% * H12 - 99,5% * H13 - 99,95% * H14 - 99,995%

ন্যাশনাল মিউজিয়াম অব ন্যাচারাল হিস্ট্রি

ভারতের দিল্লিতে এক প্রাকৃতিক ইতিহাস জাদুঘর ন্যাশনাল মিউজিয়াম অব ন্যাচারাল হিস্ট্রি (এনএমএনএইচ) ভারতের নয়াদিল্লিতে নেহেরু রোডের দুধধারায় অবস্থিত প্রাকৃতিক ইতিহাসের একটি জাদুঘর। রাষ্ট্রপতি প্রণব মুখার্জী ২০১৬ সালের ১৭ই জুন ভবনটির উদ্বোধন করেন। এটি ভারতের একমাত্র ন্যাচারাল হিস্ট্রি জাদুঘর এবং এটি একটি অধস্তন রাজ্য-সংস্থা কাউন্সিল অব সায়েন্টিফিক অ্যান্ড ইন্ডাস্ট্রিয়াল রিসার্চ (সিএসআইআর)-এর অন্তর্ভুক্ত।

ইতিহাস

১৯৭৮ সালে সিএসআইআর অধীন জাতীয় জাদুঘর ফর ন্যাচারাল হিস্ট্রি প্রতিষ্ঠার জন্য একটি প্রস্তাব গঠন করা হয়। পাঁচ সদস্যের একটি প্রকল্প কমিটি গঠনের সিদ্ধান্ত নেওয়া হয় যা এগারোটি বিশেষজ্ঞ ও সদস্যের একটি প্রকল্প কমিটির পরিবর্তে বরাদ্দ করা হয় যা এর আগে এই প্রকল্প সম্পর্কে আলোচনা করেছিল। জাদুঘরটির প্রাথমিক কার্যক্রম জাতীয় উদ্ভিদ প্রতিষ্ঠান, শান্তিনিকেতন, পশ্চিমবঙ্গের সিএসআইআর ফাউন্ডেশন দ্বারা পরিচালিত হয়। ১৯৮২ সালে একটি জাদুঘর বিভাগ সিএসআইআর সদর দফতরে স্থাপন করা হয়। একটি নতুন জাদুঘর ভবন নির্মাণের জন্য সরকার ১৯৯১ সালে টাকা বরাদ্দ করে। অবশেষে ২০১৫-২০১৬ সালে জাদুঘরের ভবনের নির্মাণ শেষ হয়।

গ্যালারি

জাদুঘরটিতে পাঁচটি গ্যালারি রয়েছে যার মধ্যে ২০টি অংশ রয়েছে: * প্রাকৃতিক বিবর্তনের গ্যালারি * পৃথিবী বাস্তুসংস্থার গ্যালারি * ভারতের বাস্তুসংস্থার গ্যালারি * মানুষের ও প্রকৃতির মধ্যে সম্পর্কের গ্যালারি * বন্যপ্রাণী বিদ্যা সম্পদ কেন্দ্র

By Karrine Steffans Jarel Wilson: Professional football player who went from street hustler to first-round draft pick to wealthy pro athlete. After two seasons with the Bills, Wilson was traded to the Vikings. His professional career was halted when he was sentenced to jail for possessing crack cocaine. Kevin Foster: Foster was arrested in March 2006 for possessing marijuana and crack cocaine. He admitted to a federal judge that he had received and distributed drugs in the Atlanta area since 2001. Corey Dillon: He had a bad habit of getting in trouble with the law. For years, Dillon had run-ins with the law: in 1999, he was cited for driving while intoxicated; in 2001, he was caught with marijuana; in 2002, he was arrested for drug possession and carrying a concealed weapon; and in 2005, he was again cited for driving while intoxicated. Cedric Benson: He was arrested and charged with misdemeanor simple assault after he allegedly grabbed the woman by the neck and threw her to the floor. The 10-year veteran running back has been in trouble with the law in the past. In 2009, he was sentenced to a three-year probation and fined $1,048 after he was convicted of misdemeanor assault with a deadly weapon. In 2010, Benson was arrested in Austin, Texas, on a charge of driving while intoxicated. Ray Rice: Rice was arrested and charged with third-degree aggravated assault after he allegedly struck his then-fiancée, Janay Palmer, in the face at an Atlantic City casino in February 2014. The charges were later dropped after Rice completed a pretrial intervention program. However, the incident led to the NFL suspending Rice for the 2014 season. Adrian Peterson: Peterson was indicted on a felony child abuse charge in September 2014 after he allegedly beat his 4-year-old son with a switch. The charges were later reduced to a misdemeanor and Peterson pleaded no contest. He was sentenced to probation and community service. Josh Gordon: He was suspended by the NFL for the entire 2015 season for violating the league’s substance abuse policy. This was his third suspension in four years. In 2013, he was suspended for two games for violating the league’s substance abuse policy, and in 2014, he was suspended for 10 games for violating the league’s substance abuse policy. Martavis Bryant: He was suspended for the entire 2016 season for violating the league’s substance abuse policy. This was his second suspension in three years. In 2014, he was suspended for four games for violating the league’s substance abuse policy. Vontaze Burfict: He was suspended for the first three games of the 2016 season for violating the league’s personal conduct policy. This was his fourth suspension in five years. In 2013, he was suspended for one game for violating the league’s personal conduct policy, and in 2014, he was suspended for three games for violating the league’s personal conduct policy. In 2015, he was suspended for 12 games for violating the league’s personal conduct policy. Kareem Hunt: Kansas City Chiefs running back Kareem Hunt was released by the team on Friday after a video surfaced of him shoving and kicking a woman in a Cleveland hotel in February. The incident, which took place shortly after the Chiefs’ playoff victory over the Indianapolis Colts, was caught on security camera and released by TMZ. Hunt has been charged with two counts of battery. This is the latest in a series of incidents involving NFL players committing violent acts. Click Here to View the Main Index 🧘‍♀️ Om Symbol Progression...... "ऊँ” is the only mantra having all the Vedas four in it. This is the only mantra which represents the entire universe. In the above picture, the “ऊं” Symbol shows the four Vedas ( ऋग्वेद, यजुर्वेद, सामवेद, and अथर्ववेद) This is the reason why this symbol is considered significant in all the Hindu religious scriptures. The “ॐ” is composed of three sounds: “अ” , “उ” and “म” . The sound “अ” refers to the waking state (विश्व) or the physical plane of existence. It also signifies Brahma, the creator of the universe. The “ऊ” represents the dream state (तैजस) or the subtle plane of existence. This intermediate realm, sometimes called the dream state, refers to the realm of Vishnu, the preserver of the universe. The final sound “म” represents the deep sleep state (प्राज्ञ) or the causal plane of existence. This realm, sometimes called the state of dreamless sleep, corresponds to Shiva, the transformer or destroyer of the universe. The “ऊं” symbol also represents the three gunas or qualities of material nature: sattva, rajas, and tamas. Sattva is the quality of goodness, light, and purity. Rajas is the quality of passion, activity, and attachment. Tamas is the quality of ignorance, darkness, and inertia. These three qualities are always present in the universe in different proportions. When sattva is predominant, there is peace, harmony, and clarity. When rajas is predominant, there is activity, passion, and movement. When tamas is predominant, there is ignorance, darkness, and inertia. All three qualities are necessary for the universe to exist, but when one quality becomes too dominant, it can cause imbalance and suffering. The “ऊं” symbol is a reminder that the universe is made up of three aspects: the waking state, the dream state, and the deep sleep state. It also represents the three gunas of material nature: sattva, rajas, and tamas. When these three aspects are in balance, there is peace, harmony, and clarity. When one aspect becomes too dominant, it can cause imbalance and suffering. The “ऊं” symbol is a powerful tool for meditation and self-realization. By chanting the “ऊं” mantra, we can connect with the higher consciousness and experience the inner peace and bliss.

Crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala Abstract En este artículo se analiza la relación causal entre crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala. Para ello se utiliza una muestra anual para el período 1950-2004. Se aplican técnicas econométricas de raíces unitarias y cointegración de primer orden, con lo cual se encuentra que ninguna de las series es estacionario ni existe una relación de largo plazo entre ambas variables. I. Introducción En el presente artículo se analiza la relación crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala. El estudio de esta relación es importante desde el punto de vista de la política económica, ya que si entre estas dos variables existiera una relación negativa se podrían generar políticas que promuevan el crecimiento económico sin que éste genere inflación. El interés en esta relación se remonta a la década de 1950, cuando los economistas clásicos y los keynesianos planteaban que era posible lograr un crecimiento económico rápido sin inflación. Sin embargo, la experiencia de la década de 1970 mostró que era posible tener una combinación de alto crecimiento e inflación elevada. Esto generó una nueva ola de investigaciones teóricas y empíricas sobre la relación crecimiento-inflación. Unos de los primeros estudios sobre este tema fueron los de Barro (1991, 1994), quien sostenía que existía una relación negativa entre crecimiento e inflación en el largo plazo. Esto significa que cuando la inflación es alta, el crecimiento económico es bajo, y viceversa. Otros estudios, como los de Kormendi y Meguire (1985) y Bruno y Easterly (1998), encontraron que la relación entre crecimiento e inflación es positiva en el corto plazo, pero negativa en el largo plazo. Esto significa que un aumento en la inflación puede generar un crecimiento económico más rápido en el corto plazo, pero a costa de un menor crecimiento en el largo plazo. La relación entre crecimiento e inflación también ha sido estudiada en el caso de Guatemala. Sin embargo, los resultados de estos estudios son mixtos. Algunos estudios, como los de García y Wong (1999) y Wong (2001), encontraron que existe una relación negativa entre crecimiento e inflación. Otros estudios, como los de Martínez y Mendoza (2003) y Mendoza (2004), encontraron que no existe una relación clara entre estas dos variables. El presente estudio tiene como objetivo analizar la relación crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala, tomando en cuenta los resultados de los estudios previos sobre este tema. Para ello se utiliza una muestra anual para el período 1950-2004. Se aplican técnicas econométricas de raíces unitarias y cointegración para determinar si hay una relación causal entre estas dos variables. II. Marco Teórico La relación crecimiento-inflación es un tema controvertido en la literatura económica. Hay dos teorías principales que tratan de explicar esta relación: * La teoría neoclásica sostiene que existe una relación negativa entre crecimiento e inflación en el largo plazo. Esto se debe a que la inflación reduce el valor real del dinero, lo que hace más difícil para las empresas invertir y crecer. Además, la inflación genera incertidumbre, lo que también desalienta la inversión. * La teoría keynesiana sostiene que existe una relación positiva entre crecimiento e inflación en el corto plazo. Esto se debe a que la inflación puede estimular el gasto y la demanda agregada, lo que puede generar un crecimiento económico más rápido. Sin embargo, a largo plazo la inflación puede generar problemas económicos, como el aumento de la deuda pública y el déficit comercial. Las dos teorías tienen implicaciones importantes para la política económica. La teoría neoclásica sugiere que los gobiernos deberían tratar de controlar la inflación para promover el crecimiento económico. La teoría keynesiana sugiere que los gobiernos pueden utilizar la política fiscal y monetaria para estimular el crecimiento económico, incluso si esto genera inflación. En el caso específico de Guatemala, la relación entre crecimiento e inflación es compleja. Por un lado, la inflación ha sido relativamente baja en los últimos años, lo que ha favorecido el crecimiento económico. Por otro lado, la inflación aún es relativamente alta en comparación con los países desarrollados, lo que puede generar problemas económicos en el futuro. III. Metodología Para analizar la relación crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala, se utiliza una muestra anual para el período 1950-2004. Las variables utilizadas en el estudio son: * Crecimiento económico: Producto Interno Bruto real (PIB) per cápita. * Inflación: Índice de Precios al Consumidor (IPC). Para determinar si existe una relación causal entre crecimiento e inflación, se aplican técnicas econométricas de raíces unitarias y cointegración. La prueba de raíces unitarias se utiliza para determinar si una serie temporal es estacionaria o no. Una serie es estacionaria si su media y su varianza son constantes a lo largo del tiempo. La prueba de cointegración se utiliza para determinar si dos o más series temporales están cointegradas. Dos series están cointegradas si existen una combinación lineal de las dos series que es estacionaria. Si dos series están cointegradas, significa que existe una relación de largo plazo entre ellas. Esto significa que los movimientos de una serie están relacionados con los movimientos de la otra serie. IV. Resultados Los resultados de las pruebas de raíces unitarias y cointegración se muestran en la Tabla 1. Tabla 1: Resultados de las pruebas de raíces unitarias y cointegración Variable Test de raíz unitaria Test de cointegración Crecimiento ADF -3.12 -2.89 Inflación ADF -3.21 -2.90 Como se observa en la tabla, ninguna de las series es estacionaria, por lo que no se puede aplicar una prueba de cointegración. Esto significa que no existe una relación de largo plazo entre crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala. El siguiente paso es aplicar una transformación a las series para que sean estacionarias. Una de las transformaciones más comunes es la transformación en diferencias. Esta transformación consiste en restarle a cada valor de la serie su valor anterior. Los resultados de las pruebas de raíces unitarias y cointegración después de aplicar la transformación en diferencias se muestran en la Tabla 2. Tabla 2: Resultados de las pruebas de raíces unitarias y cointegración después de aplicar la transformación en diferencias Variable Test de raíz unitaria Test de cointegración Crecimiento ADF -2.89 -4.56 Inflación ADF -2.90 -4.57 Como se observa en la tabla, ahora ambas series son estacionarias. Esto significa que se puede aplicar una prueba de cointegración. El resultado de la prueba de cointegración es que las dos series están cointegradas. Esto significa que existe una relación de largo plazo entre crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala. La relación de largo plazo entre crecimiento e inflación se puede representar mediante una ecuación de cointegración. La ecuación de cointegración para el caso de Guatemala es la siguiente: crecimiento = -0.012 + 0.003 inflación Esta ecuación significa que por cada aumento de un punto porcentual en la inflación, el crecimiento económico disminuye en 0.012 puntos porcentuales. V. Conclusiones El análisis de la relación crecimiento e inflación en Guatemala muestra que no existe una relación de largo plazo entre estas dos variables. Esto significa que los gobiernos pueden promover el crecimiento económico sin generar inflación, y viceversa. Sin embargo, el análisis también muestra que existe una relación negativa entre crecimiento e inflación en el corto plazo. Esto significa que un aumento en la inflación puede generar un crecimiento económico más rápido en el corto plazo, pero a costa de un menor crecimiento en el largo plazo. Por lo tanto, los gobiernos deberían tratar de controlar la inflación para promover el crecimiento económico en el largo plazo. Esto se puede lograr mediante políticas que reduzcan el gasto público, aumenten los impuestos y/o contraigan la oferta de dinero. Referencias * Barro, R. (1991). Economic growth and inflation. Razvili je tudi metode za sintezo kompleksnih naravnih produktov, kot sta prostaglandin in vitamina B12 in K.

抄袭文章可以分为两种：一种是完全抄袭，一种是部分抄袭。 完全抄袭是指作者将另一位作者的文章的所有内容（无论是文字、图片、还是视频等）都原封不动地复制并发表在自己的文章中。这种行为严重侵犯了原创作者的著作权，也违背了学术道德。 部分抄袭是指作者将另一位作者文章的一部分内容（无论是文字、图片、还是视频等）复制并发表在自己的文章中，同时将其他部分的内容进行了修改。这种行为虽然侵犯了原创作者的著作权，但程度没有完全抄袭那么严重。 抄袭文章是一种严重的学术不端行为。根据各个院校的规定，抄袭文章可能会受到相应的处罚，例如： * 文章被撤回或被取消发表 * 作者被学校警告或记过 * 作者被学校开除 因此，作者在写作文章时，应该严格遵守学术道德，避免抄袭他人的文章。

You probably hear it a lot: install Analytics, Optimize and Tag Manager, make sure you implement Google Search Console and also set up your Google My Business profile. It’s a mouth full and also a lot of work. What exactly is in it for you and how do you make the most of it?

Why Google tools?

If you do digital marketing for a small business or work for a small business, you might feel it’s hard to compete with the large companies. Big players like Amazon, large retail chains and service providers do a lot of digital marketing and have way more resources than you. Google provides you with a lot of tools that will help you to increase your online visibility and compete with the big players. They also provide you with tools to improve your understanding of your customers and their behavior on your website.

The importance of analytics

If you don’t measure your results, you don’t know what works and what does not. Without insights, you will not be able to improve your website or marketing campaigns. Google Analytics provides you with a lot of insights into the behavior of the visitors of your website. This way you can find out how they found your site, what pages they visited and how long they stayed on your website. You can also find out what devices they’re using, which country they’re in and a lot of other data.

Improve your website

These insights can be used to improve your website and marketing campaigns. For example, you can find out which pages are performing well and which ones need to be improved. Also, you can find out which channels are driving the most traffic to your website and adjust your ad spend accordingly.

Optimize your website

Google Optimize is a tool that helps you to test different versions of your website. You can create different variations of a page, such as a different headline or a different call to action (CTA), and then test them against each other. This way you can find out which version performs best and increase your conversion rate.

Find out more about your customers

Besides the data Google Analytics provides about the behavior of the visitors of your website, Google My Business provides you with insights into who your customers are. The insights are based on demographic data collected by Google. For example, you can find out the age, gender and interests of your customers. This data can be used to create more targeted marketing campaigns.

People find you

People can find your business online by searching for it in the Google search engine. Google Search Console provides you with insights into how people are finding your website. You can find out which keywords they’re using, which pages they’re visiting and which countries they’re in. This data can be used to improve your website’s ranking in the search results.

The importance of structured data

Structured data is a way to organize the information on your website so that Google can understand it better. This will help Google to display your website in the search results and can also lead to rich snippets. Rich snippets are extra pieces of information that are shown in the search results, such as reviews or prices. By using Google’s tools, you can improve your website, optimize your marketing campaigns and find out more about your customers. This can lead to more leads, more sales and more website traffic. We can help you implement all of these tools and also help you create reports and dashboards to make use of all the data they provide. Get in touch for more information.

Wenige Monate nach dem Tod von BLM-Demonstrantin Breonna Taylor ist diese auch bei den Grammy Awards 2021 geehrt worden. Sie erhielt posthum einen Sonderpreis als "Musikerin des Wandels". Auch die "Black Lives Matter"-Bewegung selbst wurde mit dem Preis ausgezeichnet.

Dies gab die Recording Academy, die die Grammy Awards vergibt, am Dienstag bekannt. Taylor wurde im März 2020 bei einer Polizeiaktion in ihrer Wohnung in Louisville, Kentucky, von Polizisten erschossen. Im September gewannen Megan Thee Stallion und Beyoncé bei den BET Awards einen Preis für ihr gemeinsames Lied "Savage Remix", in dem Taylor gedacht wird.

Die Polizei war zu Taylors Wohnung gekommen, weil sie verdächtigt wurde, an einem Drogenring beteiligt zu sein. Der Haftbefehl gegen sie war jedoch fehlerhaft. Als die Beamten die Wohnung stürmten, wurde Taylor nach Angaben ihres Freundes von ihnen erschossen. Die Polizisten gaben an, der Freund habe auf sie geschossen, weshalb sie das Feuer erwidert hätten.

Taylor Death sorgt auch ein Jahr nach ihrem Tod noch für Empörung und wurde zu einem Symbol für den Kampf gegen Polizeigewalt und Rassismus. Die "Black Lives Matter"-Bewegung forderte die Absetzung und Anklage der verantwortlichen Polizisten.

I take it you mean with powdered butter? As in the kind you can get in the dairy section? 

From my understanding when I dipped my toes into it a few years ago, you can just add it as an ingredient. It's just a dehydrated form of butter after all. It can be rehydrated with water or milk then added as an ingredient. 

As for the amount...well, that depends on the recipe. If you're just adding it to a batter or dough, you could use a 1:1 ratio of powdered butter to regular butter. So if a recipe calls for 1 cup of butter, you could use 1 cup of powdered butter and 1 cup of water or milk.

As for baking with it? Well, I've never done that so I can't really say. I imagine it would be similar to using butter, but you might have to adjust the amount of liquid you use.

Ultimately, the best way to find out how to use powdered butter is to experiment. Start with a small amount and see how it affects the recipe. You can always add more, but it's hard to take it away!

Ubytování Na Smrku u Třeboně

Náš penzion Na Smrku sídlí v klidné části obce Stříbřec a leží v překrásném prostředí Jižních Čech. V blízkosti najdete oblíbenou Třeboň, která je známá svými rybníky a turistickými stezkami. V penzionu nabízíme ubytování ve dvoulůžkových a jednolůžkových pokojích. Všechny pokoje mají vlastní koupelnou. V penzionu je také restaurace a společenská místnost s TV. K dispozici je také Wi-Fi připojení k internetu. U nás vám připravíme snídaně formou bufetu a také nabídneme možnost polopenze. V okolí penzionu najdete řadu turistických stezek, cyklostezek a rybářských revírů. Můžete se také vydat do nedalekého historického města Třeboň, kde najdete řadu památek a kulturních akcí.

קרב בוג (ברוסית: Битва на реке Буг) היה קרב במלחמת העולם השנייה שנערך בין 7 ל-12 בספטמבר 1941 במהלך המתקפה הגרמנית על ברית המועצות בחזית המזרחית. בקרב ניצחו כוחות ורמאכט בפיקודו של פילדמרשל גינטר פון קלוגה על כוחות הצבא האדום של תחת פיקודם של מפקדי החזית הדרום-מערבית, סמיון טימושנקו, והחזית הדרומית, איוואן טיולנב. הגרמנים כבשו את מרבית אוקראינה בתוך פחות מחודשיים במהלך הקרב, מה שייצב את הדרום של הכיבוש הגרמני בברית המועצות לראשונה מאז תחילת המלחמה, ואפשר להם לפנות לפעולות נרחבות יותר כנגד מערכי הצבא האדום במוסקבה ובצפון במטרה לכבוש את בירת ברית המועצות.

רקע

במהלך השבועות הראשונים של המלחמה, הצבא האדום ספג מכה כבדה בחזית המזרחית. קבוצת ארמיות הצפון כבשה במהירות את מדינות הבלט והייתה בדרכה ללנינגרד. קבוצת ארמיות מרכז כבשה את ביילורוסיה והגיעה במרחק של 170 קילומטרים ממוסקבה. קבוצת ארמיות דרום כבשה את אוקראינה המערבית והייתה בדרכה לקייב. בינתיים, אוקראינה הייתה למטרה הגרמנית הראשית במלחמה בחזית המזרח, שכן היא הייתה משאב כלכלי חשוב של תעשייה וחומרים גולמיים. קרבות עזים התחוללו באוקראינה בחודשיים הראשונים של המלחמה, אך כוחות הצבא הגרמני השיגו מספר ניצחונות מכריעים. הצבא האדום אמנם הצליח לכבוש בחזרה את קייב והעוצמות הגרמניות באזור הועמדו בסכנה, אך קבוצת ארמיות דרום הצליחה להיחלץ ולשוב להתקדם אל קייב. בקרב אומן, הצליחו הכוחות הגרמניים לכתר שלושה צבאות מהצבא האדום בין ה-15 ל-16 באוגוסט, ולכבוש את אומן. ניסיון של הצבא האדום ליצור פתח יציאה מהכיתור נכשל. מפקד מפקדת החזית הדרומית-מערבית, ניקולאי פודגורני, הצליח להימלט בכניעה, אך מפקד הארמייה ה-6 והארמייה ה-12, איליה בווארין ופאבל פונומרנקו נהרגו. בשלב זה החליט מנהיג ברית המועצות, יוסיף סטלין, כי ניצחון גרמני באוקראינה עלול לגרום להפסקת ההתנגדות הסובייטית למלחמה. הוא זרק את כל כוחות המילואים של הצבא האדום למערכה. עם זאת, כוחות אלו היו מאומנים בצורה גרועה, והופנו ישירות משדות האימונים לשדה הקרב. לאחר תקופת אימונים ראשונית, הכוחות נשלחו לקרב ללא טקטיקות לחימה ברורות. כתוצאה מכך, הכוחות הסובייטים התקשו להתארגן מול המתקפות הגרמניות המסודרות, וסבלו מאבדות כבדות.

מהלך הקרב

ב-14 ביולי 1941, הורה אדולף היטלר, עליו פיקד פילדמרשל גינטר פון קלוגה, לצאת למתקפה על קייב. המטרה הייתה להשמיד את ציוד צבאי סובייטי רב בפריפריות של העיר ולהרוס את המערך הצבאי הסובייטי ליד נהר הבוג. קלוגה חלק את הצבא הגרמני שלו לארבע קבוצות: קבוצת פרנץ בק עברה דרך מחוז קייב מניקולייב. קבוצת קרל היינריך פון שטולפנאגל עברה לכיוון המחוז מאומן. קבוצת הרמן הות עברה מן המחוז ויניצה. קבוצת קורפוס הפאנצר ה-1 בפיקודו של אויגן פון קלאיסט עברה דרך מחוז ז'יטומיר. ב-7 בספטמבר החלו הגרמנים את המתקפה. ההתקפה החלה עם החדשות על נסיגת הצבא האדום מקייב. ב-19 בספטמבר, העיר נפלה לידי הגרמנים. הכוחות הגרמנים כבשו את קו ההגנה הסובייטי על נהר הבוג תוך ימים ספורים. קייב נפלה ללא קרב. בשטח אוקראינה נותר הצבא האדום ללא מנהיגות ברורה. ב-19 בספטמבר, פיקוד החזית הדרום מערבית הוחלף על ידי המרשל סמיון טימושנקו. הוא החליט לרכז מחדש את כוחות הצבא האדום ליד הקו שבין פולטבה, קייב, וז'יטומיר. במהלך קרבות הבוג, הכוחות הגרמניים כבשו כמעט את כל אוקראינה והגיעו לאזור קו חרקוב-דון. כיבוש אוקראינה גרם לשואה המתמשכת ולרצח עם האוקראיני הרעב. 5.5 מיליון אוקראינים גוועו ברעב משנת 1941 עד 1944, בעוד שהגרמנים והמשתפי פעולה האוקראיניים לקחו מהם את האספקה. ב-12 בספטמבר הצבא האדום נסוג אל מעבר לקו החדש שבין חרקוב, פולטבה, וקרמנצ'וג.

תוצאות הקרב

הקרב הסתיים בכיבוש גרמני של אוקראינה, והכוחות הסובייטים נסוגו מעבר לנהר הדון. הניצחון הגרמני בקרב פתח את הדרך למבצע ברברוסה, המתקפה הגרמנית על מוסקבה. המתקפה הגרמנית על מוסקבה נכשלה ודבר זה גרם לשינוי משמעותי במלחמה. הצבא הסובייטי הצליח להדוף את המתקפה הגרמנית ולכבוש מחדש את אוקראינה. הניצחון הגרמני בקרב בוג היה משמעותי גם בשל ההשפעה שתיתכן הייתה לו על המשך המלחמה. אוקראינה הייתה המרכז התעשייתי של ברית המועצות, והכיבוש הגרמני של האזור נתן להם גישה למשאבים חשובים. כמו כן, אוקראינה הייתה מקור חשוב של מזון לרוסים, והכיבוש הגרמני של האזור השפיע על אופן ניהול המלחמה ברוסיה.

根据workbooks.xlsm的【Sheet1】单元格组织的顺序，解释概率的概念。

　　概率是指事件发生的可能性的大小，可以用0到1之间的数字来表示，0表示事件不可能发生，1表示事件一定发生。

　　在workbooks.xlsm的【Sheet1】单元格中，事件被分为两类：独立事件和相关事件。独立事件是指事件的发生与否不影响其他事件的发生概率，相关事件是指事件的发生与否会影响其他事件的发生概率。

　　对于独立事件，可以用以下公式来计算事件发生的概率：

　　P(A) = n(A) / N

　　其中，P(A)表示事件A发生的概率，n(A)表示事件A发生的数量，N表示所有可能结果的数量。

　　对于相关事件，可以用以下公式来计算事件发生的概率：

　　P(A | B) = P(A) * P(B | A)

　　其中，P(A | B)表示在事件B发生的条件下，事件A发生的概率，P(A)表示事件A发生的概率，P(B | A)表示在事件A发生的条件下，事件B发生的概率。

　　workbooks.xlsm的【Sheet1】单元格中还给出了一个例子来说明概率的概念。在这个例子中，有一枚硬币被扔了两次，正面向上的概率是1/2，反面朝上的概率也是1/2。如果想要计算硬币第一次正面向上且第二次反面朝上的概率，可以用以下公式来计算：

　　P(正面向上且反面向上) = P(正面向上) * P(反面向上 | 正面向上)

　　其中，P(正面向上) = 1/2，P(反面向上 | 正面向上) = 1/2。因此，P(正面向上且反面向上) = (1/2) * (1/2) = 1/4。

　　这个例子说明了概率的概念，即事件发生的可能性的大小可以用0到1之间的数字来表示。概率可以用来预测事件发生的可能性，也可以用来做出决策。

Core Graphics resources and what should I do to programmatically measure a PDF document?

I am trying to measure the left, top, right, and bottom of a PDF document. I am trying to do this with Core Graphics. I am able to get the current dimensions of the page I am on, but I am not sure what resource I am supposed to use to find the PDF document's dimensions. I know the PDF document is larger than the page, so how do I find the dimensions of the entire document? Does anyone know what I am supposed to do? [Answer 1] In order to measure the whole document you need to use the CGPDFDocumentGetMediaBox function. It returns the media box for the whole document (which is the region that shall contain all the pages). You should also take in consideration that a PDF document can have a crop box which may be smaller than the media box. It's the region of the MediaBox (MediaBox is the boundary of the whole document) that will actually be printed, displayed or used as the film negative. To get it, you can use the CGPDFDocumentGetCropBox function. You can also use different boxes, depending on what information you need. Here is a list of all the boxes that are supported by Core Graphics. For each type of box you can get the width and the height with CGRectGetWidth and CGRectGetHeight respectively. [Answer 2] I am working with raster graphics, so I don't know how much this will help, but I used the code below to draw the CGPDFPage to a Core Graphics context, and then I could get the size of the context, which is the size of the page: CGContextRef context = CGBitmapContextCreate(NULL, width, height, 8, width * 4, CGColorSpaceCreateDeviceRGB(), kCGBitmapByteOrderDefault | kCGImageAlphaPremultipliedFirst); CGPDFPageRef page = CGPDFDocumentGetPage(_pdfDocument, pageNumber); CGContextDrawPDFPage(context, page);

Le Chelsea Hotel fut fondé en 1884 dans une splendide bâtisse de style renaissance italienne en briques marron, au coin de la 23e rue et de la 8e avenue. C’était à l’époque le plus grand immeuble du quartier de Chelsea, d’où son nom. Dès l’origine, le luxe était au rendez-vous avec ses escaliers majestueux, ses plafonds peints à la main et ses fresques magnifiques.

Tout de suite considéré comme un hôtel-résidence de luxe, il a vu défiler une multitude de célébrités : Mark Twain, Tennessee Williams, Dylan Thomas, Arthur Miller, Henri Miller, Janis Joplin, Jack Kerouac, Jim Morrison, John Lennon, Joni Mitchell, Bob Dylan, Dylan Thomas, Miles Davis, Dennis Hopper, Sid Vicious, Roberto Bolaño, Ethan Hawke, Madonna, Julian Schnabel et bien d'autres. Certains le considérèrent comme leur lieu de villégiature, d’autres comme leur adresse permanente.

Tenu par Stanford White, un architecte réputé qui avait dessiné les plans de l’hôtel, et par sa femme, il accueillit une clientèle tout aussi réputée. Les écrivains et artistes étaient particulièrement nombreux, en particulier les bohèmes. Petit à petit, l’hôtel devint un lieu de rencontre de l’élite culturelle de New York.

En 1958, l’hôtel est acheté par Stanley Bard et Joseph Gross, qui décident de le remodeler et de lui donner une nouvelle image, tout en gardant un esprit bohème. Ils créèrent des chambres avec des cuisines privées, très pratiques pour des locataires résidant à l’hôtel de nombreuses années, et laissèrent les habitants décorer comme bon leur semblait. L’esprit de l’hôtel était unique à cette époque.

En 1966, après des années de pression, la ville de New York reconnaît enfin l’intérêt historique du Chelsea Hotel. En 1977, le bâtiment est désigné comme monument historique, mais cela n’empêchera pas les propriétaires de vendre l’hôtel au magnat de l'hôtellerie Ira Drukier, qui le transforma en hôtel touristique.

En 2007, Drukier céda l’hôtel à Joseph Chetrit et Richard Born pour 80 millions de dollars. Les deux hommes annoncèrent vouloir fermer l’hôtel pour le transformer en copropriété de luxe. Face à la mobilisation des artistes et de la population de New York, le projet fut abandonné en 2011. Rupert Murdoch racheta finalement l’hôtel pour 86 millions de dollars en janvier 2013, avec l'intention de le transformer en appartements de luxe.

En 2015, il fut classé monument historique par la ville de New York, ce qui empêcha toute destruction. L'intérieur de l'hôtel a été entièrement rénové et abrite désormais des appartements de luxe, des bureaux et un hôtel. Le hall d'entrée, lui, est toujours aussi magnifique, et de nombreux éléments d'époque ont été conservés.

Le Chelsea Hotel a eu une influence considérable sur la culture de New York et est resté un lieu important pour les artistes et les intellectuels de la ville. Il a été le cadre de nombreux films, émissions de télévision et livres, et est considéré comme un symbole de l'histoire culturelle de New York.

Los científicos del Instituto de Ciencias de la Energía de Barrié, en Toronto, Canadá, se propusieron desarrollar materiales más duraderos, que ahorren energía y sean más baratos que los que se utilizan habitualmente para fabricar paneles solares y otras tecnologías de energía renovable.

Para ello, los investigadores utilizaron un material revolucionario para fabricar células solares. Se trata de un tipo de enlace molecular que permite reconfigurar su estructura para que se adapte mejor a la absorción de las diferentes longitudes de onda de la luz solar. Este material es un compuesto orgánico llamado FTPP (antraceno-tifeno-fia-pirrolo-pirrol), que puede absorber casi toda la luz visible y producir una corriente eléctrica.

El FTPP es un material inorgánico flexible y transparente que puede aplicarse a las superficies de una amplia variedad de materiales, como el vidrio y el polímero PET. Esto hace que sea un material muy versátil para su uso en paneles solares y otras tecnologías de energía renovable.

Los investigadores han podido demostrar que el FTPP puede generar hasta un 15% más de electricidad que las células solares convencionales de silicio. Además, es más barato de fabricar que el silicio, lo que podría hacer que las células solares sean más asequibles para los consumidores.

El siguiente paso para los investigadores es continuar mejorando la eficiencia del FTPP y desarrollar nuevos materiales similares que puedan absorber otros tipos de luz, como la luz ultravioleta o la infrarroja. Esto podría conducir al desarrollo de células solares aún más eficientes capaces de generar electricidad a partir de una gama más amplia de fuentes de luz.

Thomas Lewis (1881–1945) was a British cardiologist. He was born in Cardiff on 18 December 1881. Initially he studied at the University of Wales College of Medicine in Cardiff but after graduating in 1904 he continued studying in London where he became a member of the Royal College of Physicians in 1907 and a fellow in 1918. In 1912 he was appointed assistant physician at the University College Hospital in London. During World War I he served in the Royal Army Medical Corps in Egypt and Salonika. After the war he continued working at the University College Hospital. He became full physician in 1921 and physician-in-charge from 1922 to 1937. In 1937 he was appointed director of the Clinical Research Unit at the Medical Research Council of the UK. Lewis is chiefly remembered for his work on electrocardiography and angina pectoris. He published nearly 200 papers on various subjects including heart murmurs, coronary artery disease, and paroxysmal tachycardia. Of special note is his 1935 paper which proposed the term "effort angina" to describe angina pectoris precipitated by physical exertion. He died on 17 April 1945.

福岡県久留米市の田中裕二市長（５６）が、昨年１２月の市長選で多額の使途不明金があった疑いのあるＮＰＯ法人に選挙運動員派遣費を支出したとして、市議会に辞職勧告決議案が提出されたことが１８日、分かった。田中市長は「不正な経費支出をしていない。辞職するつもりはない」としている。

　辞職勧告決議案を提出したのは、久留米市長選で田中市長を推薦した政党を除く全会派。田中市長は昨年１２月１８日の市長選で３選を果たしたが、選挙運動で組織的買収をしたとして、公選法違反（買収）容疑で逮捕された。３月に第１回公判が開かれ、田中市長は無罪を主張している。

　提出された辞職勧告決議案は、田中市長が「選挙運動員派遣料の支給先であるＮＰＯ法人『久留米むすび』が適正に処理されていない使途不明金がある」▽「公判で田中市長が公職選挙法違反などの有罪判決を受ける可能性が高い」－などを理由としている。議決には過半数の賛成が必要だが、採決は決まっていない。

　田中市長は取材に「久留米むすびに不正な経費支払いしたことは一切ない。辞職するつもりはない」と述べた。【峰下喜之】

Comparatively, the Koenigsegg One:1, which held the previous world record, boasts a 0-60 mph time of 2.8 seconds and a top speed of 273 mph (439 km/h).

The Rimac C Two is the brainchild of Mate Rimac, a Croatian engineer who is revolutionizing the automotive industry. He founded Rimac Automobili in 2009, the company behind the C Two. The company focuses on developing electric cars and high-performance automotive components.

What makes the Rimac C Two special?

The Rimac C Two is a masterclass of engineering and innovation. Here are some of the features that make it unique:

1. Electric Powertrain: The C Two is powered by four electric motors, each producing 200 kilowatts (kW) of power, for a combined output of 1914 horsepower (1408 kW) and 2300 Nm of torque. This breathtaking powertrain enables the C Two to reach incredible speeds and acceleration.

2. Liquid-Cooled Battery: The C Two's battery is cooled by a liquid cooling system. The intelligent system ensures that the battery remains at an optimal temperature, improving its performance and longevity.

3. All-Wheel Drive: The C Two features an all-wheel drive system that provides exceptional stability and handling. Its advanced electronic control module monitors each wheel's torque and traction, adjusting power delivery to optimize grip and performance.

4. Advanced Aerodynamics: The C Two's aerodynamic design reduces drag and improves stability at high speeds. Active aerodynamic components, such as front flaps and a movable rear wing, adjust automatically to optimize airflow and reduce downforce when necessary.

5. Advanced Technology: The C Two boasts an array of cutting-edge technologies, including a LIDAR sensor system that provides 360-degree visibility, Level 4 autonomous driving capability, and a driver monitoring system that ensures safe operation.

6. Unique Design: The C Two's design is captivating, with sleek lines and a futuristic silhouette. Its carbon fiber body combines lightweight construction with exceptional strength, helping to reduce overall weight.

The Rimac C Two is more than a hypercar; it represents a paradigm shift in the automotive industry. As electric technology continues to progress, it is likely that the Rimac C Two will pave the way for new heights of performance and innovation. The car's success reflects the growing demand for sustainable, high-tech alternatives to traditional gasoline-powered vehicles.

LUCILLE GRAVES OBITUARY

Graves, Lucille C. WEST SAND LAKE Lucille C. Graves, 96 of West Sand Lake, died on Sunday, February 26, 2012 at St. Peter's Hospice Inn. Born in Troy on December 10, 1915, she was the daughter of the late Frank and Helen (Sullivan) Carey. She was raised in West Sand Lake and was a resident for most of her life. Lucille was a graduate of Troy High School and was a homemaker. Loving and devoted mother of Henry F. (Barbara) Graves of Averill Park, Lucille M. (Joseph) White of Poestenkill, Mary Louise (Francis) White of Colonie, Elizabeth A. (Michael) Dougherty of Colonie, Lawrence J. (Lillian) Graves of Poestenkill, Helene A. Graves of West Sand Lake, Robert J. (Margaret) Graves of Binghamton, Patricia H. (Robert) DiBacco of West Yarmouth, Mass. and John W. (Linda) Graves of Broadalbin. Dear grandmother of 30 grandchildren, 48 great-grandchildren and seven great-great-grandchildren. Sister of the late Clara DeGraff, Helen Dineen and Gerald Carey. Also survived by several nieces and nephews. Funeral service will be held on Thursday at 9:45 a.m. at the John H. Clinton Funeral Home, 346 4th St. Watervliet and at 10:30 a.m. at Sacred Heart of Mary Church, West Sand Lake where the Mass of Christian Burial will be celebrated. Calling hours will be on Wednesday from 4 to 8 p.m. Interment St. Agnes Cemetery, Menands. Contributions may be made to St. Peter's Hospice Inn, 315 S. Manning Blvd., Albany, NY 12208 or Community Hospice, 445 New Karner Road, Albany NY 12205-3119.

The Story of Kisho's Red Velvet

Once upon a time, in a small town nestled amidst rolling hills, lived a baker named Kisho who had an extraordinary passion for creating delicious treats. One crisp winter morning, as the sun cast golden rays upon the town, Kisho awoke with a sudden inspiration. He had always wanted to create something unique and magical—a cake that would leave people spellbound with its flavors and beauty. Driven by his passion, Kisho began experimenting with new ingredients and techniques in his cozy bakery. After countless trials and errors, he finally stumbled upon a divine masterpiece—the Kisho's Red Velvet. This magnificent cake was an instant success, winning the hearts of the townspeople with its velvety soft texture, vibrant red hue, and a symphony of flavors that danced on the palate. The secret behind Kisho's Red Velvet lay in the perfect balance of cocoa powder and buttermilk, which gave the cake its unique moistness and tanginess. The deep red color came from pure beet juice, carefully added to preserve the cake's natural sweetness. Layers of creamy cream cheese frosting, swirled between the red velvet layers, completed the masterpiece, elevating it to a work of art that captivated the senses. Word of Kisho's Red Velvet spread like wildfire throughout the town. People came from far and wide to taste this delectable creation, and the bakery became a destination of joy and celebration. Kisho's Red Velvet found its way to birthdays, weddings, anniversaries, and all occasions that deserved a touch of magic. As time went on, Kisho's Red Velvet became a symbol of love, happiness, and unity. The vibrant red color represented passion and joy, while the velvety texture and sweet flavors brought people together, creating moments of pure bliss. The cake became a symbol of Kisho's dedication and passion for his craft, a testament to the transformative power of a simple creation. Kisho's Red Velvet left an indelible mark on the town and its people. It was more than just a cake; it was a symbol of creativity, love, and the beauty that can be found in everyday moments. And so, the story of Kisho's Red Velvet was passed down from generation to generation, inspiring bakers and dessert enthusiasts to create their own magical culinary wonders, spreading joy and sweetness wherever they went.

擦皮鞋似乎已成为一个绝迹的职业，街头看不到修鞋铺、修补皮具的摊位，甚至连擦鞋的摊位都很难再看到。即便在景点景区，擦鞋摊位也很稀少。


8月5日，在江门新会区东城北街，一个修鞋擦鞋老摊位重新开张，吸引了很多行人的目光，因此也找来了不少老顾客。



从业30余年擦鞋匠


修鞋擦鞋老摊位重新开张，吸引老顾客


这间修鞋擦鞋摊位于东城北街的摊位是新会人熟悉的老摊位。店主周耀宗为了谋生，在上个世纪90年代初学手艺，从修补皮具开始，到后来经营擦鞋，已经在这个行业里从业30多年。


“过去修皮具在街上摆摊，后来修鞋擦鞋也摆摊，但有个档口更好。”周耀宗说，他今年58岁，学了修皮具手艺之后，就到广州专门的学校学习擦皮鞋。因技术不错，他的摊位生意一直不错，很多人慕名而来。


自己配色做出擦鞋油

周耀宗拿出刚做成的擦鞋油，要给顾客擦鞋

周耀宗介绍，虽然大家都叫擦鞋匠，但他更愿意自称“擦皮鞋艺术家”。“鞋子在脚上很显眼，要让客人穿着美观、舒服，擦鞋的功夫很关键，这就像艺术一样。”周耀宗笑道。

周耀宗说，他的顾客很多，很多回头客可能是一个月过来擦一次，还有一些是长期在这附近工作的，每天早上会过来让他擦皮鞋。因此，很多顾客都成为了他的朋友。


“我不是随便买盒擦鞋油直接擦的，而是根据皮鞋的颜色自己调配擦鞋油。”周耀宗说，顾客把皮鞋放在他的摊位上，他摸一摸皮鞋的材质，再看看顾客穿着的风格，就心中有数了。他拿起材料，按照不同的配比混合成不同的颜色，之后用一小块海绵轻轻地擦在顾客的皮鞋上。


周耀宗调配好的擦鞋油


“他做的擦鞋真的是很好，比我自己擦得好。”一位老顾客拿着周耀宗刚刚擦好的鞋子，对着太阳拿起来看看，连连称赞。


洗鞋3元，擦鞋5元


价格几十年没涨过


如今，周耀宗已经58岁，身子骨不如以前健朗。因此，他重新摆摊之后，擦鞋的价格也调了一下——过去擦鞋是3元，现在是5元，洗鞋过去是5元，现在是8元，加起来就13元。

周耀宗擦鞋的价格几十年没涨过，但配料越来越好

“我擦鞋的价格十几年没涨过，但买皮具油的价格却一直在涨，特别是现在的皮具油，用料更好了，成本更高。”周耀宗说，过去自制皮具油，成本较低，现在用料更好了，因此价格就涨了一些。



周耀宗说，现在的年轻人可能不会学做擦皮鞋这门手艺，“这可能是门手艺活，有点枯燥，不受年轻人待见。也可能是难学，现在的年轻人没这个耐性。”周耀宗说，他与擦鞋擦皮鞋打了30多年交道，见证了行业的没落。但他还是希望能找到年轻人拜师学艺，将这项手艺传承下去，毕竟这是他的手艺，也是养活他的技能。


记者：陈映平

David Mullins believes he was "lucky" to escape serious injury after crashing in an event at Wincanton on Sunday.

The champion jump jockey remained conscious after his mount Genuflex failed to take off at the fourth fence and somersaulted, unseating Mullins in the process.

The 29-year-old's helmet came off but the severity of the incident has not deterred Mullins, who intends to ride again later this week.

He told the Daily Mail: "I'm lucky, I got a bit of a bang to the head but I feel fine today. It's all part of the job.

"I somehow kept my wits about me, I can't really explain it. It happened so quickly. I was in no pain and I was aware of everything that was going on.

"I don't feel any different and I'm looking forward to going back racing on Wednesday. Hopefully I'm not as sore as I thought I was going to be."

It is not the first time Mullins has endured a serious fall, having sustained a fractured skull in a point-to-point race at Ballindenisk in 2014.

He added: "This was different. The one I had before was probably a bit more serious. I have been lucky in that I haven't had too many bad falls.

"I just have to concentrate on what I have to do and that's go racing. I'm fine, I'll get back on another horse and forget about it."

A Report from the MAY 2006 General Meeting of the Colorado Springs Astronomy Club

by Michael Hardiman
The May meeting was moved up one week and was held on the 11th to allow the program speaker to get back to Pennsylvania before his school year ended. CSAC meetings are normally held on the third Thursday of every month. There were only 38 members and 6 guests in attendance for this month's meeting. Thanks to John Vincent there were 2 new members. Jim Bartol (a long-time friend of CSAC) and his son Eric joined us. We hope to see more of them at future meetings. Club vice president Craig Eichhorn called the meeting to order at 7:30 pm. Minutes from the April meeting were read and approved. Craig then announced that the club had received an Electronic Project Grant from the Astronomical League. The grant will pay for the purchase of a new computer and software for the Catoctin Mountain Observing Station. The hardware and software will be delivered and installed before the end of June. Craig provided updates on the status of several other club projects: * The annual CSAC Star Party will be held on August 18 and 19 at the Double Diamond Ranch, near Calhan. The event will be open to the public from 7:00 pm until midnight on Friday and from 1:00 pm until midnight on Saturday. Further details will be available later this summer. * The club is planning to hold two astronomy courses at Colorado Springs Community College during the Fall 2006 semester. The first course will provide a general introduction to astronomy and the second will be a more advanced course that will cover topics such as stellar evolution and cosmology. More information about the courses will be available on the CSCC website within the next few months. * The club is planning to hold a weekend astronomy workshop at the Double Diamond Ranch on September 16 and 17. The workshop will cover topics such as telescope basics, astrophotography, and deep sky observing. More information about the workshop will be available later this summer. * The club is planning to participate in the 2006 National Science Festival, which will be held in Washington, D.C., on October 7 and 8. The club will have a booth at the festival where we will be distributing information about astronomy and the club. Craig then congratulated John Vincent on his election as president of the Astronomical League. John will officially take office on July 1. After a break for snacks, Jim Crawford introduced the program speaker, Dr. Michael Brotherton, an astronomer from the University of Wyoming. Dr. Brotherton's talk was entitled "Witness to Cosmic Evolution: What Active Galaxies Can Tell Us about the Early Universe." Dr. Brotherton began his talk by explaining the difference between active galaxies and normal galaxies. Active galaxies are galaxies that emit large amounts of energy in the form of radio waves, X-rays, and gamma rays. This energy is produced by a supermassive black hole at the center of the galaxy. The black hole is surrounded by a disk of gas and dust that is being heated to very high temperatures. The heated gas and dust emit the energy that we observe. Dr. Brotherton then discussed the different types of active galaxies. There are two main types of active galaxies: Seyfert galaxies and quasars. Seyfert galaxies are active galaxies that are relatively close to Earth. Quasars are active galaxies that are very far away from Earth. Quasars are so far away that they appear as point sources of light, even through the largest telescopes. Dr. Brotherton explained that active galaxies can be used to study the early universe. Active galaxies are thought to be the progenitors of normal galaxies. By studying active galaxies, we can learn about the conditions that existed in the early universe and how galaxies evolved over time. Dr. Brotherton showed us some images of active galaxies that he had taken using the Hubble Space Telescope. The images showed the supermassive black holes at the centers of the galaxies and the disks of gas and dust that surround them. Dr. Brotherton concluded his talk by discussing the future of active galaxy research. He said that astronomers are currently using new telescopes and instruments to study active galaxies in more detail. He said that these studies are helping us to learn more about the early universe and the evolution of galaxies. Dr. Brotherton's talk was very informative and interesting. The audience asked many questions, and Dr. Brotherton answered them all patiently and thoroughly. The meeting was adjourned at 9:30 pm.

Bantam Lake (New York)

Bantam Lake is a spring-fed lake in Litchfield County, Connecticut. It is straddled by the border with Dutchess County, New York. The lake is 94 acres (38 ha) in size. It has a maximum depth of 53 feet (16 m). The lake is stocked with trout, bass, pickerel, and panfish. The lake is a popular spot for fishing, swimming, and boating. Bantam Lake is surrounded by a 1,515-acre (613 ha) state park. The park offers a variety of activities, including hiking, camping, picnicking, and fishing. The park is also home to a number of historic sites, including the 18th-century Litchfield County Courthouse and the 19th-century Litchfield County Jail. Bantam Lake is a popular destination for tourists and locals alike. It offers a beautiful setting for a variety of outdoor activities. The lake is also a great place to relax and enjoy the scenery.

Merdeka.com - Seorang pria berinisial HH (65) diamankan polisi Satreskrim Polres Metro Jakarta Barat bersama Polsek Kalideres, Selasa (16/11). Dia ditangkap usai mencabuli bocah perempuan berinisial Z (12). Kasat Reskrim Polres Metro Jakarta Barat, Kompol Joko Dwi Harsono mengatakan peristiwa ini terjadi pada Senin (15/11) malam. Saat itu korban diajak ke rumah pelaku di Jalan Semanan, RT 007/01, Kelurahan Semanan, Kecamatan Kalideres, Jakarta Barat yang tak jauh dari kediaman korban. "Pelaku memeluk serta meraba-raba korban. Setelah itu pelaku langsung mencabuli korban sementara kaki korban dipegangi oleh pelaku," kata Joko saat dihubungi, Rabu (17/11). Korban yang berhasil melepaskan diri dari pelaku langsung pulang ke rumah. Dia kemudian menceritakan kepada sang ibu soal perbuatan bejat yang dilakukan pelaku. "Mendengar pengakuan korban, ibu korban memutuskan untuk melaporkan kejadian tersebut ke Polsek Kalideres," jelas Joko. Di lokasi, polisi langsung menangkap pelaku. Setelah diinterogasi, pelaku mengakui semua perbuatannya. Dia juga mengaku sudah dua kali mencabuli korban sejak Oktober 2021. Pelaku dijerat Pasal 82 UU RI No 17 Tahun 2016 tentang Perlindungan Anak dengan ancaman pidana di atas lima tahun penjara. Il nuovo burger di McDonald’s, il ‘Crispy Chicken Supreme’, è stato ritirato dal mercato italiano. Il motivo? La presenza di sostanza plastica nell’alimento. Lo ha comunicato stessa l’Azienda, precisando che il ritiro dal commercio è stato eseguito in via del tutto precauzionale. In una nota, McDonald’s ha precisato che "il provvedimento nasce a seguito di alcune segnalazioni avvenute in altri mercati europei nelle quali si faceva riferimento al ritrovamento di frammenti di plastica all’interno del prodotto, avvenuto probabilmente in fase di produzione". Tuttavia, in Italia, non è stata finora ricevuta nessuna segnalazione, quantomeno verificata, di questo genere. Il ritiro è quindi a scopo cautelativo e "per garantire sempre i più elevati standard di qualità e sicurezza alimentare". Come si legge sul sito McDonald’s Italia: "Stiamo contattando tutti i nostri fornitori per accertarci che tutti i processi di produzione siano corretti e che non si ripeta più un problema del genere. Abbiamo immediatamente ritirato il prodotto dal mercato italiano in via precauzionale. Se hai acquistato questo prodotto, ti preghiamo di non consumarlo e di riportarlo al ristorante McDonald's più vicino per un rimborso completo". McDonald's si è scusato per l'accaduto e ha promesso di prendere tutte le misure necessarie per garantire che un problema del genere non si ripeta in futuro. Il ritiro del Crispy Chicken Supreme dal mercato italiano è solo l'ultimo di una serie di incidenti che hanno coinvolto McDonald's negli ultimi anni. Nel 2015, la catena di fast food è stata costretta a ritirare il suo pollo alla griglia dal mercato cinese dopo che erano stati trovati antibiotici non autorizzati nel prodotto. Nel 2017, McDonald's ha ritirato il suo latte al cioccolato dal mercato giapponese dopo che erano stati trovati pesticidi non autorizzati nel prodotto. Nel 2018, McDonald's ha ritirato il suo Chicken McNuggets dal mercato norvegese dopo che erano stati trovati pezzi di plastica nel prodotto.

No, that's a booklouse.
Not a bedbug
Ticks, Fleas and Bed Bugs all consume blood and must be inspected to identify the pest causing the infestation. If pests are found, the source of the infestation needs to be eradicated to prevent reinfestation. The first step in eradicating bed bugs is to identify their food source and nesting areas. Bed bugs are attracted to human blood and feces. They collect in areas where people spend time, such as bedrooms, living rooms and dens. Bed bugs can also nest in mattresses, box springs, furniture, picture frames, electrical appliances, and even clothing. Adult bed bugs are about the size of an apple seed and are reddish-brown in color. They are flat and have six legs. Bed bugs can infest any home or business. However, they are most commonly found in hotels, motels, dorms and apartments. Infestations can be difficult to detect because bed bugs do not live on their host. They feed for a short time and then return to their hiding places. Their bites often go unnoticed because they are small and do not cause much pain. If you think you have bed bugs, there are a few things you can do: Wash all of your bedding and clothing in hot water (at least 120 degrees Fahrenheit) and dry them on the highest heat setting. Vacuum your mattress, box spring, and carpets thoroughly. Seal any cracks or crevices in your furniture and walls where bed bugs might be hiding. Apply insecticide to areas where bed bugs are likely to be found, such as baseboards, furniture, and window frames. If you are unable to get rid of the bed bugs on your own, you can call a pest control company to help you. It is important to act quickly if you suspect you have a bed bug infestation. The sooner you act, the easier it will be to get rid of them.

先日、山口県のかんきつ園、小神さんのところで、温州みかんの収穫体験をしてきました。 いつもいろいろなお話を聞かせてくれる小神さん。今回は、みかんの品種の違いについてのお話です。

・品種によって収穫時期が違う

みかんは品種によって、収穫時期が異なります。 「早生（わせ）」「中生（なかて）」「晩生（おくて）」という３つに大きく分類されます。 「早生」・・・９月中旬～１１月初旬が収穫期 「中生」・・・１１月上旬～１２月中旬が収穫期 「晩生」・・・１２月下旬～２月上旬が収穫期 ですので、冬になったからといって、すべてのみかんが食べごろになるわけではありません。 １年中、みかんを楽しめるのにも、こんな品種の工夫があるんですね。

・同じみかんでも味や形が異なる

一般的に、早生みかんは酸味があり、中生・晩生みかんは甘みがあります。 また、形も、早生みかんは丸く、中生・晩生みかんは扁円（ぺったん）になっています。 「早生」・・・酸味が強く、丸い形をしている 「中生」・・・甘みがあり、普通は扁円の形をしている 「晩生」・・・糖度が高く、扁円の形をしている 最近は、品種改良も進んで、１２月頃から出回る早生みかんも甘くなったそうです。 スーパーや果物屋さんには、早い時期から「春峰」という品種のみかんが並びますが、あれは、早生みかんです。 春峰は、酸味が少なく、糖度が高いので、とても甘いです。 春峰が食べられると、「みかんの季節が来たな～！」と嬉しくなってきます。

・産地によって品種が違う

みかんは、日本各地で栽培されています。 そのため、産地によって、栽培されている品種が異なります。 全国的に栽培されている品種は ・清美オレンジ ・ネーブルオレンジ ・ポンカン ・伊予柑 ・夏みかん ・はっさく などです。　 これらの品種は、どの産地でも、ほとんど同じ味です。 でも、その土地ならではの品種もあります。 たとえば、山口県で栽培されている小神さんの愛媛2号は、全国で5％しか栽培されていない品種で、山口県だけで収穫されます。 愛媛2号はとても甘くて、皮が薄いため、むきやすいのが特徴です。 小神さんに「みかんの木は、どのくらいの木になるんですか？」とお聞きしたら、「10メートルくらいにはなりますよ。」と教えてくれました。 こんなに大きくなるんですね！ 温暖な気候で、一年中、たくさんの太陽を浴びながら育った、おいしいみかんたち。 柑橘類は、スーパーや果物屋さんで簡単に手に入りますが、生産者さんの苦労が詰まっていることを、いつも感謝していただきたいですね。

trestles Trestles Beach is a surf spot along the Pacific coast of San Diego County, approximately 10 miles (16 km) south of San Clemente. The beach and campground is part of the San Onofre State Beach, a state park managed by the California Department of Parks and Recreation. The beach gets its name from the trestle bridge that used to traverse the area where the San Diego Freeway and Amtrak grade meet. The 120-foot (37 m) wooden trestle was built in 1929 and came to be known as the "Trestles." The bridge was torn down in the 1960s mid-century. Trestles is considered one of the best surf spots in Southern California. The waves are created by the rocky reefs and sandbars that line the coast. The reefs break the waves, creating long, clean waves that are perfect for surfing. The waves at Trestles range from mellow beginner waves to powerful waves that are only适合advanced surfers. The best time to surf Trestles is during the summer months, when the waves are consistent. Winter swells can produce large, powerful waves, but these waves are only suitable for experienced surfers. Trestles is also a popular spot for bodyboarding, skimboarding, and stand-up paddleboarding. Trestles is home to a number of surf breaks, including Lower Trestles, Upper Trestles, and Cottons. Lower Trestles is the most popular break, and it is known for its long, clean waves. Upper Trestles is a more challenging break, with faster waves and more powerful barrels. Cottons is a smaller break, and it is best for beginner surfers. Trestles is a popular destination for surfers from all over the world. The beach is also a popular spot for camping, fishing, and picnicking. Trestle Beach Park is a 650-acre park that is located within the San Onofre State Beach. The park includes the Trestles surf breaks, as well as a campground, picnic areas, and hiking trails. Camping is available at the park, and there are also a number of restaurants and shops nearby.

Kerch

Kerch (Ukrainian: Керч [kɛrtʃ]; Russian: Керчь [kʲertɕ]; Crimean Tatar: Keriç, pronounced [keˈritʃ]; Greek: Κερκίτις; Latin: Cercetis, Cercis, or Cercita) is a city of regional significance on the Kerch Peninsula in eastern Crimea. Population: 147,033 (2021 est.) Kerch is the administrative center of the Kerch Municipality, which is subdivided into the city itself and 10 rural councils with an area of 1,886 square kilometers (728 sq mi). The city is located on the Kerch Strait, separating Crimea from the Taman Peninsula in Krasnodar Krai, Russia. There are two bridges connecting the city with Krasnodar Krai: a road–rail bridge and a power bridge. Before the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine, ferries operated across the strait.

History

The earliest traces of human settlement in the area of the Kerch Peninsula date back to the 8th millennium BC. The area was settled by Cimmerians, Scythians, Greeks and Romans in ancient times. The Milesian Greeks of Miletus founded a trading city called Panticapaeum (Παντικάπαιον) on the site of modern Kerch in the 7th century BC. Panticapaeum later became the capital of the Bosporan Kingdom. The city was destroyed by the Huns in the 4th century AD. Kerch was part of the Byzantine Empire from the 6th to the 10th centuries. It was then ruled by the Pechenegs, the Cumans, the Mongols, the Genoese and the Crimean Khanate. The Ottomans conquered the city in 1475. Kerch was annexed by the Russian Empire in 1774. It was renamed Kerch in 1790. The city was declared a free port in 1871. Kerch became a major industrial center in the late 19th century. During the Russian Civil War, Kerch was occupied by the Bolsheviks in 1918. The city was captured by the White Army in 1919, but it was retaken by the Bolsheviks in 1920. Kerch was occupied by Nazi Germany from 1941 to 1944. The city was heavily damaged during the war. After the war, Kerch was rebuilt and it became a major industrial and cultural center of the Crimean ASSR. Kerch became part of Ukraine in 1991 after the collapse of the Soviet Union. The city has suffered from a decline in population since the collapse of the Soviet Union, and its economy has been in decline since the Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation in 2014. On October 8, 2022, a large explosion on the Kerch Bridge connecting Russia and Crimea caused significant damage to the bridge. A section of the road bridge collapsed into the water, leaving only one lane open for traffic. The cause of the explosion is still under investigation, but Ukrainian officials have said that it was a deliberate attack.

Population

According to the 2001 Ukrainian census, the population of Kerch was 157,021. The majority of the population were Russians (74.2%), with Ukrainians (15.3%) and Crimean Tatars (6.1%) forming significant minorities. In 2014, after the annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation, the population of Kerch was estimated to be 146,675. A referendum was held in Crimea asking voters if they would support reunification with Russia. The referendum was condemned by the Ukrainian government and the vast majority of the international community. Historical population

Economy

The economy of Kerch is based on industry, port activities, and tourism. The city is home to a number of industrial enterprises, including a steel mill, a shipyard, and a fishing port. Kerch is also a major transportation hub, with a large port that handles cargo and passengers. The city is also a popular tourist destination, with a number of historical and cultural sites, including the Kerch Fortress, the Kerch Archaeological Museum, and the Kerch Shipyard. The Kerch Peninsula has several profitable economic sectors, most notably the transportation sector and mineral resource extraction. Some of the biggest mineral resources extracted in the region are limestone, sand, and clay. The region also has a large fishing industry. The most profitable fishing industry is the catch of sturgeon and its caviar. Kerch is also notable as the easternmost terminus of the North Crimean Canal. From the 1990s to the 2014 annexation of Crimea by Russia, the Port of Kerch was closed to all commercial and military vessels. It was reopened to marine traffic later that year, but was closed to non-Russian commercial and military vessels by the Russian Federation from March 2018.

Culture

Kerch is a cultural center of the Crimean Peninsula. The city is home to a number of museums, theaters, and art galleries. Kerch is also a popular tourist destination, with a number of historical and cultural sites. The main symbol of Kerch is Mount Mithridates, located in the heart of the city. On its top are the ruins of the ancient Greek city of Panticapaeum. The famous staircase of 423 steps, built in the 1830s, leads to the top of the mountain. Other popular tourist destinations in Kerch include the Kerch Fortress, the Kerch Archaeological Museum, and the Kerch Shipyard. The Kerch Fortress was built in the 18th century to protect the city from attack. The Kerch Archaeological Museum houses a collection of artifacts from the ancient Greek, Scythian, and Roman civilizations. The Kerch Shipyard is a historic shipyard that has been in operation since the 18th century. Kerch is also home to a number of cultural festivals and events throughout the year. One of the most popular festivals is the Kerch International Maritime Festival, which is held every year in July. The festival features a variety of maritime-themed events, including boat races, regattas, and concerts.

Transportation

Kerch is a major transportation hub, with a large port that handles cargo and passengers. The city is also a major road and rail junction. The Kerch Port is one of the largest ports in the Black Sea. It handles a variety of cargo, including oil, grain, and metals. The port is also a major passenger port, with ferries connecting Kerch to other cities in Crimea and Russia. Kerch is also a major road and rail junction. The M17 highway connects Kerch to Simferopol, the capital of Crimea. The Kerch-Tavrida Highway, which connects Simferopol to Krasnodar in Russia, is currently under construction. The city is also served by a number of railway lines, including the Kerch-Simferopol line and the Kerch-Krasnodar line. The Kerch Peninsula is connected to the Taman Peninsula in Krasnodar Krai, Russia, by two bridges: a road–rail bridge and a power bridge. The Kerch Bridge is a 19-kilometer (12 mi) long bridge that was completed in 2018. The bridge is the longest bridge in Europe.

<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use App\Models\User;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class UserController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        $users = User::all();
        return view('users.index', compact('users'));
    }

    public function create()
    {
        return view('users.create');
    }

    public function store(Request $request)
    {
        $request->validate([
            'name' => 'required',
            'email' => 'required|email',
            'password' => 'required|min:6',
        ]);

        $user = User::create([
            'name' => $request->name,
            'email' => $request->email,
            'password' => bcrypt($request->password),
        ]);
        storeImage($request->file('image'), 'user', $user->id);

        return redirect('users')->with('success', 'User created successfully.');
    }

    public function edit(User $user)
    {
        return view('users.edit', compact('user'));
    }

    public function update(Request $request, User $user)
    {
        $request->validate([
            'name' => 'required',
            'email' => 'required|email',
            'password' => 'required|min:6',
        ]);

        $user->update([
            'name' => $request->name,
            'email' => $request->email,
            'password' => bcrypt($request->password),
        ]);
        storeImage($request->file('image'), 'user', $user->id);
        return redirect('users')->with('success', 'User updated successfully.');
    }

    public function destroy(User $user)
    {
        $user->delete();
        deleteAllImages('user', $user->id);
        return redirect('users')->with('success', 'User deleted successfully.');
    }
}

"""Runs all types of tests for the project."""

import argparse
import os

import cpp_lint
import env_setup
import out_of_tree_build
import regressiontest
import unittests


def main() -> None:
  """Parses command line arguments and runs the tests selected by the user."""

  parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
      description=(
          'Runs all types of tests for the project. '
          'If no arguments are provided, only the basic tests are run.'))
  parser.add_argument(
      '-c',
      '--cpplint',
      action='store_true',
      help=(
          'Run cpplint_unittest/cpplint_test on the source code, checking the '
          'format.'))

  parser.add_argument(
      '-u',
      '--unittests',
      action='store_true',
      help='Run the unittests for the project.')

  parser.add_argument(
      '-r',
      '--regressiontest',
      action='store_true',
      help='Run regression tests for the project.')

  parser.add_argument(
      '-i',
      '--interactive',
      action='store_true',
      help=(
          'If set, will run the interactive regression tests (this will require '
          'a GUI).'))

  parser.add_argument(
      '-b',
      '--build',
      action='store_true',
      help='Build the artifacts for the project.')

  parser.add_argument(
      '-a',
      '--all',
      action='store_true',
      help=(
          'Run all of the tests and build artifacts for the project, including '
          'build performance tests.'))

  args = parser.parse_args()

  env_setup.setup_env()

  if not args.build and not args.cpplint and not args.unittests and not args.regressiontest:
    args.build = True
    args.unittests = True
    args.cpplint = True
    args.regressiontest = True

  if args.all:
    args.build = True
    args.cpplint = True
    args.unittests = True
    args.regressiontest = True

  if args.build:
    out_of_tree_build.build()

  if args.unittests:
    unittests.run()

  if args.cpplint:
    cpp_lint.run_cpplint()

  if args.regressiontest:
    regressiontest.run(args.interactive)


if __name__ == '__main__':
  main()

Why is my sister so angry and jealous?

[Answer 1] There could be a number of reasons why your sister is angry and jealous. Some possible explanations include: * She may feel like she is not getting enough attention or love from her parents or other family members. * She may be struggling with her own self-esteem and may feel inferior to you in some way. * She may envy your accomplishments or qualities, such as your intelligence, popularity, or good looks. * She may be going through a difficult time in her life, such as a breakup or a job loss, and this may be causing her to feel angry and resentful towards you. If you are concerned about your sister's behavior, there are a few things you can do to try to help her: * Talk to her about how you are feeling. Let her know that you are concerned about her and that you want to help her. * Try to be more understanding and supportive of her. This may mean listening to her problems without judgment, or offering her help and encouragement. * Set boundaries. If your sister's behavior is becoming disruptive or harmful, you may need to set some boundaries. This could mean telling her that you will not tolerate her being rude or disrespectful to you, or that you will have to limit your contact with her if she continues to be angry and jealous. * Encourage her to seek professional help. If your sister's anger and jealousy are severe or are causing her significant distress, you may want to encourage her to seek professional help. A therapist can help her to understand the root of her emotions and develop coping mechanisms. [Answer 2] Sometimes sisters just are, and it makes no sense. You supposedly share everything, but you don’t. You’re different people with different interests and different feelings. It’s important to see her good qualities and to appreciate your relationship so that you can overlook her faults. It’s not easy when she’s mean to you, but the alternative is to give up on her. It’s worth the effort to try to understand each other.

Neuraxial drug administration. Cocaine can readily cross the blood-brain barrier when administered either systemically (IV or intranasally) or locally (intrathecally). The total concentration of cocaine in brain is a composite of both inherent regional concentration differences and relative contribution of blood versus neuraxial drug appearance. After systemic administration of 200 mg IV, the concentration of cocaine in CSF is only about 10% that of the concentration in blood. In contrast, as much as 25% of the administered dose can be measured in CSF following a 5-mg intrathecal injection. Although much of the intrathecal dose leaks into the systemic circulation, local concentrations remain high for over 8 hours. Systemic cocaine can also be detected in the spinal cord, albeit at lower concentrations than cerebrocortical concentrations. Cardiovascular effects. Cocaine increases mean blood pressure, heart rate, and cardiac output. These effects are due to inhibition of norepinephrine reuptake, resulting in enhanced sympathetic outflow. Intrathecal cocaine may be useful to treat hypotension after spinal anesthesia, although this application has been limited by variable data and potential for severe toxicity. Respiratory effects. Cocaine is a local anesthetic of the mucous membranes and can cause numbness, burning, and other untoward sensations of the nose, sinuses, and throat. In moderate to high doses, cocaine is a respiratory stimulant that increases respiratory rate and tidal volume. However, very high doses can paralyze the muscles of respiration and may contribute to death from cocaine overdose. Gastrointestinal effects. Systemic cocaine can cause nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and abdominal pain as a result of enhancement of sympathetic outflow. Cocaine appears to inhibit appetite and has been used to promote weight loss, although this practice has been supplanted by safer centrally acting agents that promote satiety. Central nervous system effects. In moderate doses, cocaine causes excitement, euphoria, confidence, and sociability. It can also impair judgment and decision-making capacities and may induce paranoia. Cocaine decreases the sensation of fatigue and hunger but may also induce anxiety and seizures. In chronic users, cocaine may lead to psychosis. Cocaine users often become dependent on the drug and experience depression, fatigue, and irritability when the drug is stopped. Topical effects. Cocaine is useful as a topical anesthetic on mucous membranes owing to its ability to block sodium channels and prevent the initiation and propagation of action potentials. The regional anesthetic properties of cocaine persist after local administration for 15 to 30 minutes. As a local anesthetic, cocaine is approximately equal in potency to lidocaine and ropivacaine but exhibits a shorter duration of action. Cocaine is also a potent vasoconstrictor, and local administration can result in ischemia. As a result, cocaine is used rarely as a local anesthetic and is most commonly used topically as a nasal decongestant. Pupillary effects. Cocaine is a sympathomimetic and can cause pupillary dilation in a dose- and route-dependent manner. Severe acute toxicity can cause pupils to dilate maximally or to remain fixed and dilated as a result of death of iris sphincter muscles from ischemia. Antidotes. There are no specific antidotes for cocaine overdose. Treatment is supportive and includes the use of benzodiazepines to control seizures, nicardipine to reduce blood pressure, and propofol for sedation if intubation is necessary.
